00:26:35.780 --> 00:26:37.340 align:middle line:90%
that they give people.

00:26:37.340 --> 00:26:38.910 align:middle line:90%
That's an amazing story.

00:26:38.910 --> 00:26:43.160 align:middle line:84%
It tells us exactly
that what you're saying

00:26:43.160 --> 00:26:45.410 align:middle line:90%
is absolutely the truth.

00:26:45.410 --> 00:26:47.840 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: I think it also
tells us what a human being is.

00:26:47.840 --> 00:26:50.420 align:middle line:84%
Because, I think, we're
put here on this planet

00:26:50.420 --> 00:26:51.860 align:middle line:90%
as students of life.

00:26:51.860 --> 00:26:52.790 align:middle line:90%
We're here to learn.

00:26:52.790 --> 00:26:54.230 align:middle line:90%
Our body wants to learn.

00:26:54.230 --> 00:26:55.760 align:middle line:90%
Our mind wants to learn.

00:26:55.760 --> 00:26:58.130 align:middle line:84%
So that's why we're never
meant to do the same thing

00:26:58.130 --> 00:26:59.810 align:middle line:90%
over and over and over again.

00:26:59.810 --> 00:27:01.580 align:middle line:84%
And the one thing
about the narcotics

00:27:01.580 --> 00:27:03.260 align:middle line:84%
that we're taking
to correct all the

00:27:03.260 --> 00:27:06.320 align:middle line:84%
hormonal issues or
the wandering mind--

00:27:06.320 --> 00:27:09.320 align:middle line:84%
it's taking-- it's robbing
the children of the ability

00:27:09.320 --> 00:27:12.050 align:middle line:84%
to be able to step into
that power on their own.

00:27:12.050 --> 00:27:13.810 align:middle line:84%
And meditation is
the exact opposite.

00:27:13.810 --> 00:27:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Meditation is
allowing that child

00:27:16.670 --> 00:27:20.810 align:middle line:84%
to calm themselves down and
find a self-soothing routine.

00:27:20.810 --> 00:27:24.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: In terms of
exercise, what do you do?

00:27:24.050 --> 00:27:27.240 align:middle line:84%
And is it different from
what people generally do?

00:27:27.240 --> 00:27:28.040 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Yeah.

00:27:28.040 --> 00:27:31.550 align:middle line:84%
Because exercise is typified
by repetitious movement,

00:27:31.550 --> 00:27:34.010 align:middle line:84%
like going on a treadmill,
doing the same thing.

00:27:34.010 --> 00:27:36.550 align:middle line:90%
Or overworking vanity muscles--

00:27:36.550 --> 00:27:37.490 align:middle line:90%
monkey see, monkey do.

00:27:37.490 --> 00:27:39.650 align:middle line:84%
We see other people,
you know, bench pressing

00:27:39.650 --> 00:27:40.790 align:middle line:90%
and stuff like that.

00:27:40.790 --> 00:27:42.380 align:middle line:84%
But that's overworking
some muscles

00:27:42.380 --> 00:27:45.230 align:middle line:84%
and forgetting about the
core stabilizer muscles.

00:27:45.230 --> 00:27:46.910 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
definition of imbalance.

00:27:46.910 --> 00:27:49.460 align:middle line:90%
So what I mean is not--

00:27:49.460 --> 00:27:53.630 align:middle line:84%
it's not a method to look better
or to lose weight or detox.

00:27:53.630 --> 00:27:57.290 align:middle line:84%
Really, what it's meant to do is
to get you to move differently,

00:27:57.290 --> 00:27:59.870 align:middle line:84%
explore different loads
that you put on the body.

00:27:59.870 --> 00:28:02.480 align:middle line:84%
Because this is how your
body opens itself up

00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:06.200 align:middle line:84%
to intelligence from the
environment, to embody itself.

00:28:06.200 --> 00:28:07.540 align:middle line:90%
And then we can access it.

00:28:07.540 --> 00:28:09.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's where the
intelligence-- that's

00:28:09.290 --> 00:28:11.330 align:middle line:84%
how we embody it and
it turns into wisdom,

00:28:11.330 --> 00:28:14.450 align:middle line:84%
is when we've embodied the
knowledge that we have.

00:28:14.450 --> 00:28:18.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And is it an
unusual series of exercises?

00:28:18.550 --> 00:28:19.654 align:middle line:90%
Is it hard to learn?

00:28:19.654 --> 00:28:20.570 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Not really.

00:28:20.570 --> 00:28:24.140 align:middle line:84%
It's actually much more
primal than you would imagine.

00:28:24.140 --> 00:28:26.000 align:middle line:90%
You know, I mean, for one--

00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:27.350 align:middle line:90%
go out and climb a tree.

00:28:27.350 --> 00:28:29.810 align:middle line:84%
There's so much
dynamics and rich,

00:28:29.810 --> 00:28:33.440 align:middle line:84%
you know, dynamics in a tree,
that you won't find in a gym.

00:28:33.440 --> 00:28:35.600 align:middle line:10%
And you know that
a pull-up bar is

00:28:35.600 --> 00:28:37.730 align:middle line:10%
going to hold you, because
some person made sure

00:28:37.730 --> 00:28:38.896 align:middle line:10%
that it's going to hold you.

00:28:38.896 --> 00:28:40.190 align:middle line:90%
But a branch-- you don't know.

00:28:40.190 --> 00:28:42.470 align:middle line:84%
So there's all this
problem-solving.

00:28:42.470 --> 00:28:44.360 align:middle line:84%
Climbing a tree,
going rock climbing,

00:28:44.360 --> 00:28:46.400 align:middle line:84%
swimming through
natural water outside,

00:28:46.400 --> 00:28:48.320 align:middle line:84%
which is typically a lot
colder than the water

00:28:48.320 --> 00:28:49.850 align:middle line:90%
that we like to be in.

00:28:49.850 --> 00:28:52.940 align:middle line:84%
Moving through nature
is, more or less,

00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:53.900 align:middle line:90%
what I'm talking about.

00:28:53.900 --> 00:28:57.510 align:middle line:84%
Because working out in a gym
is not a learning environment

00:28:57.510 --> 00:28:58.310 align:middle line:90%
for the brain.

00:28:58.310 --> 00:29:00.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And the location
of where you do this--

00:29:00.470 --> 00:29:01.610 align:middle line:90%
is it important?

00:29:01.610 --> 00:29:03.080 align:middle line:84%
Because I know,
for example, when

00:29:03.080 --> 00:29:05.330 align:middle line:84%
you do some of these
exercises, you're

00:29:05.330 --> 00:29:06.916 align:middle line:90%
out in the woods somewhere.

00:29:06.916 --> 00:29:10.110 align:middle line:90%


00:29:10.110 --> 00:29:11.296 align:middle line:90%
So what are you doing here?

00:29:11.296 --> 00:29:13.170 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Well, this
is actually Ben Medder.

00:29:13.170 --> 00:29:15.810 align:middle line:84%
He's a natural movement
coach in the UK.

00:29:15.810 --> 00:29:18.600 align:middle line:84%
Soon we'll see me getting
into different exercises.

00:29:18.600 --> 00:29:21.975 align:middle line:84%
But here, this is just exploring
how the body has to move around

00:29:21.975 --> 00:29:23.100 align:middle line:90%
differently through nature.

00:29:23.100 --> 00:29:24.660 align:middle line:90%
This is me and my daughter.

00:29:24.660 --> 00:29:26.220 align:middle line:90%
And, you know, these--

00:29:26.220 --> 00:29:27.575 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's the exercise?

00:29:27.575 --> 00:29:28.980 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: These are
some of the exercises.

00:29:28.980 --> 00:29:30.940 align:middle line:84%
And, basically-- and
this is the ice bath.

00:29:30.940 --> 00:29:33.000 align:middle line:84%
It's not the most
fun thing to do.

00:29:33.000 --> 00:29:36.030 align:middle line:84%
But it really engages
the body in the same way

00:29:36.030 --> 00:29:37.290 align:middle line:90%
that our ancestors had to.

00:29:37.290 --> 00:29:39.570 align:middle line:84%
Because they had
to-- in the winter--

00:29:39.570 --> 00:29:42.000 align:middle line:84%
wade through water to
go catch their fish.

00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:43.620 align:middle line:84%
And they had to
climb through trees

00:29:43.620 --> 00:29:46.495 align:middle line:84%
to survey the landscape, to see
where predator or prey might

00:29:46.495 --> 00:29:47.295 align:middle line:90%
be.

00:29:47.295 --> 00:29:49.335 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How often are
you doing that, every day?

00:29:49.335 --> 00:29:50.010 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Every day.

00:29:50.010 --> 00:29:50.810 align:middle line:90%
Every day.

00:29:50.810 --> 00:29:52.942 align:middle line:84%
And I don't suggest
that everyone

00:29:52.942 --> 00:29:54.150 align:middle line:90%
should be doing it every day.

00:29:54.150 --> 00:29:57.390 align:middle line:84%
I say, we should start
introducing it into our lives

00:29:57.390 --> 00:30:01.106 align:middle line:84%
and discovering the inspiration
that it'll give you.

00:30:01.106 --> 00:30:03.480 align:middle line:84%
I'm not telling people, you
need to do five hours of this

00:30:03.480 --> 00:30:04.385 align:middle line:90%
a week.

00:30:04.385 --> 00:30:06.510 align:middle line:84%
It should tell you how much
you should be doing it.

00:30:06.510 --> 00:30:08.700 align:middle line:84%
But we should definitely
be moving our bodies a lot

00:30:08.700 --> 00:30:09.825 align:middle line:90%
more than we are now.

00:30:09.825 --> 00:30:11.825 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So that's what
you're basically doing--

00:30:11.825 --> 00:30:14.602 align:middle line:84%
you're moving your body
with those exercises--

00:30:14.602 --> 00:30:16.560 align:middle line:84%
because rolling-- throwing
the ball in the air,

00:30:16.560 --> 00:30:18.965 align:middle line:84%
moving around like that,
and stuff like that.

00:30:18.965 --> 00:30:21.000 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Yeah, because--

00:30:21.000 --> 00:30:24.820 align:middle line:84%
I won't get into the ultra
minutiae of the science of it.

00:30:24.820 --> 00:30:27.127 align:middle line:84%
But everything that
you saw up there is--

00:30:27.127 --> 00:30:29.460 align:middle line:84%
they're different loads that
you're placing on the body.

00:30:29.460 --> 00:30:31.590 align:middle line:84%
They're different
manipulations of the body.

00:30:31.590 --> 00:30:35.130 align:middle line:84%
And what that does is that sends
new information to the cells.

00:30:35.130 --> 00:30:37.470 align:middle line:84%
And if the cells aren't
getting new information,

00:30:37.470 --> 00:30:39.249 align:middle line:84%
then they're not in
their optimal form.

00:30:39.249 --> 00:30:41.040 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I'm
talking about-- getting

00:30:41.040 --> 00:30:42.970 align:middle line:84%
into our optimal
form-- so opening up

00:30:42.970 --> 00:30:44.330 align:middle line:90%
to the information of nature.

00:30:44.330 --> 00:30:46.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I know some
people who will go to work;

00:30:46.980 --> 00:30:51.870 align:middle line:84%
come home and have dinner; get
on the couch; grab the clicker;

00:30:51.870 --> 00:30:53.760 align:middle line:90%
start watching television.

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:56.190 align:middle line:84%
Then they go to bed, if
they haven't passed out

00:30:56.190 --> 00:30:57.510 align:middle line:90%
on the couch.

00:30:57.510 --> 00:30:59.445 align:middle line:84%
What kind of a
lifestyle is that?

00:30:59.445 --> 00:31:02.370 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Well, that
shows you that movement,

00:31:02.370 --> 00:31:04.290 align:middle line:84%
to people like
that, is just a way

00:31:04.290 --> 00:31:06.120 align:middle line:84%
to get from one
sitting position--

00:31:06.120 --> 00:31:08.760 align:middle line:84%
or one relaxed
position-- to another.

00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:11.310 align:middle line:84%
And this is completely
the opposite from what

00:31:11.310 --> 00:31:12.170 align:middle line:90%
our ancestors--

00:31:12.170 --> 00:31:13.650 align:middle line:90%
they hardly ever sat down.

00:31:13.650 --> 00:31:15.510 align:middle line:84%
And when they did,
they were squatting.

00:31:15.510 --> 00:31:20.130 align:middle line:84%
So, nowadays, really, we
have so much furniture

00:31:20.130 --> 00:31:22.400 align:middle line:84%
that tells us, that
beckons us, come lay down.

00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:24.840 align:middle line:84%
Get as comfy as
you possibly can.

00:31:24.840 --> 00:31:26.910 align:middle line:84%
But we don't really
set our houses up

00:31:26.910 --> 00:31:29.362 align:middle line:90%
to move in many different ways.

00:31:29.362 --> 00:31:31.320 align:middle line:84%
We have the steps to help
us get up the stairs.

00:31:31.320 --> 00:31:32.825 align:middle line:90%
But that's about it.

00:31:32.825 --> 00:31:34.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's talk about
it in terms of age, Ben.

00:31:34.970 --> 00:31:36.090 align:middle line:90%
If you're in your 20s--

00:31:36.090 --> 00:31:38.670 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to elevate
up to 60 or 70 here--

00:31:38.670 --> 00:31:41.000 align:middle line:84%
but when you're in your
20s, what should you

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:42.427 align:middle line:90%
be doing lifestyle-wise?

00:31:42.427 --> 00:31:44.760 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Well, because you
can bounce back so quickly,

00:31:44.760 --> 00:31:47.880 align:middle line:84%
I would say, really experiment
with the three major things

00:31:47.880 --> 00:31:49.980 align:middle line:84%
that I tell people to do--
is focus on your diet,

00:31:49.980 --> 00:31:52.080 align:middle line:84%
focus on your movement
and your posture,

00:31:52.080 --> 00:31:56.400 align:middle line:84%
and also focus on the
celebration and the fun aspect

00:31:56.400 --> 00:31:57.480 align:middle line:90%
that you bring into it.

00:31:57.480 --> 00:31:59.880 align:middle line:84%
So, for people in
their 20s, I would say,

00:31:59.880 --> 00:32:01.680 align:middle line:90%
move through nature a lot more.

00:32:01.680 --> 00:32:04.830 align:middle line:84%
Try some ice baths, some things
that really challenge you.

00:32:04.830 --> 00:32:06.840 align:middle line:84%
And the point that this
is not, again, to get

00:32:06.840 --> 00:32:09.590 align:middle line:90%
all buff and good looking.

00:32:09.590 --> 00:32:12.960 align:middle line:84%
It's to teach your body how to
deal with stressful situations.

00:32:12.960 --> 00:32:15.140 align:middle line:84%
Because there's an
intrinsic reward--

00:32:15.140 --> 00:32:17.020 align:middle line:84%
dopamine and different
things like that.

00:32:17.020 --> 00:32:19.560 align:middle line:84%
But there's also the
intelligent reward in that.

00:32:19.560 --> 00:32:23.610 align:middle line:84%
And, also, if you fast or if you
try dieting every now and then,

00:32:23.610 --> 00:32:25.320 align:middle line:84%
your body is going
to deal with hunger.

00:32:25.320 --> 00:32:27.360 align:middle line:84%
And we typically freak
out when we're hungry,

00:32:27.360 --> 00:32:30.110 align:middle line:84%
but ancestors-- they used
to go days without eating.

00:32:30.110 --> 00:32:32.790 align:middle line:84%
And it wouldn't freak them
out, because they understood

00:32:32.790 --> 00:32:36.330 align:middle line:84%
that this is just a signal from
the body telling us something.

00:32:36.330 --> 00:32:37.350 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 30s to 40s.

00:32:37.350 --> 00:32:38.850 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: From
that point, you want

00:32:38.850 --> 00:32:41.520 align:middle line:84%
to start taking a look at
how you're bouncing back

00:32:41.520 --> 00:32:42.390 align:middle line:90%
from injuries.

00:32:42.390 --> 00:32:45.040 align:middle line:84%
And you want to be more
intelligent about biomechanics.

00:32:45.040 --> 00:32:46.620 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just
about moving more,

00:32:46.620 --> 00:32:48.267 align:middle line:90%
it's moving more intelligently.

00:32:48.267 --> 00:32:50.100 align:middle line:84%
You want to learn how
to bend over properly.

00:32:50.100 --> 00:32:52.800 align:middle line:84%
You want to learn how
to kneel down and squat.

00:32:52.800 --> 00:32:55.770 align:middle line:84%
Posture-- learning posture is
probably the number one thing

00:32:55.770 --> 00:32:58.680 align:middle line:84%
we should be doing
throughout our life,

00:32:58.680 --> 00:33:01.980 align:middle line:84%
is learning how to
stand and sit correctly,

00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:05.290 align:middle line:84%
so all of our tissues
are un-inhibiting--

00:33:05.290 --> 00:33:07.215 align:middle line:90%
or not inhibiting blood flow.

00:33:07.215 --> 00:33:09.045 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 40s to 60.

00:33:09.045 --> 00:33:10.350 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: 40s to 60s--

00:33:10.350 --> 00:33:11.306 align:middle line:90%
it's the same thing.

00:33:11.306 --> 00:33:13.680 align:middle line:84%
We're just now getting up into
the point where you really

00:33:13.680 --> 00:33:16.562 align:middle line:84%
need to start making sure
you're not overdoing it.

00:33:16.562 --> 00:33:17.520 align:middle line:90%
A lot of people think--

00:33:17.520 --> 00:33:18.795 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So maybe
not as intense.

00:33:18.795 --> 00:33:19.878 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Not as intense.

00:33:19.878 --> 00:33:21.972 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of the
times people ran marathons

00:33:21.972 --> 00:33:23.430 align:middle line:84%
five years ago and
they still think

00:33:23.430 --> 00:33:25.763 align:middle line:84%
they're in that kind of shape,
but they haven't done it.

00:33:25.763 --> 00:33:28.710 align:middle line:84%
So, really, just pay more
attention to your body.

00:33:28.710 --> 00:33:31.710 align:middle line:84%
And this is-- honestly, when
you're getting up there in age,

00:33:31.710 --> 00:33:34.410 align:middle line:84%
it's a great opportunity to
start listening to your body

00:33:34.410 --> 00:33:35.370 align:middle line:90%
more.

00:33:35.370 --> 00:33:37.500 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you're out
in public and someone

00:33:37.500 --> 00:33:40.320 align:middle line:84%
might come up to you and say,
god, you look good today.

00:33:40.320 --> 00:33:42.690 align:middle line:90%
You look refreshed.

00:33:42.690 --> 00:33:44.950 align:middle line:84%
And they see something,
obviously, right?

00:33:44.950 --> 00:33:46.950 align:middle line:90%
Or they wouldn't have said that.

00:33:46.950 --> 00:33:48.960 align:middle line:90%
Does that mean it's working--

00:33:48.960 --> 00:33:50.535 align:middle line:84%
whatever you're
doing, it's working?

00:33:50.535 --> 00:33:51.660 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: I believe it is.

00:33:51.660 --> 00:33:54.330 align:middle line:84%
And even that,
specifically, that's

00:33:54.330 --> 00:33:58.050 align:middle line:84%
also a testament that
we are optimistic,

00:33:58.050 --> 00:33:59.640 align:middle line:90%
and optimism, and celebration.

00:33:59.640 --> 00:34:02.790 align:middle line:84%
I, very much so, get into the
shamanic aspect of this, which

00:34:02.790 --> 00:34:04.860 align:middle line:90%
is adding ceremony into it.

00:34:04.860 --> 00:34:06.270 align:middle line:90%
So it's not just moving out--

00:34:06.270 --> 00:34:08.400 align:middle line:84%
moving for the sake
of moving and dieting

00:34:08.400 --> 00:34:11.570 align:middle line:84%
for the sake of dieting, but
it's putting them all together

00:34:11.570 --> 00:34:14.570 align:middle line:84%
and holding it and focusing
it on an intention.

00:34:14.570 --> 00:34:17.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's why people will
say, you look good today,

00:34:17.060 --> 00:34:19.250 align:middle line:90%
because you're open to nature.

00:34:19.250 --> 00:34:21.679 align:middle line:84%
You're not inhibiting the
intelligence of nature

00:34:21.679 --> 00:34:24.050 align:middle line:84%
to come in, and you're
attuning with nature.

00:34:24.050 --> 00:34:26.401 align:middle line:84%
And that will give you all
the energy that you need.

00:34:26.401 --> 00:34:30.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: While human beings are
adaptable; they're intelligent;

00:34:30.000 --> 00:34:33.920 align:middle line:84%
they're geniuses when it
comes to certain things.

00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:38.600 align:middle line:84%
In your film, "Ungrip," you
take a look at human ingenuity.

00:34:38.600 --> 00:34:39.779 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing.

00:34:39.779 --> 00:34:42.679 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Human ingenuity
can surmount any obstacle.

00:34:42.679 --> 00:34:46.340 align:middle line:84%
The only requirement is
the desire to surmount.

00:34:46.340 --> 00:34:49.219 align:middle line:84%
If we are willing to complain
or rebel against the system that

00:34:49.219 --> 00:34:53.929 align:middle line:84%
governs our actions, we should
know how and why it does so.

00:34:53.929 --> 00:34:57.530 align:middle line:84%
In doing this, it is important
to understand who we are,

00:34:57.530 --> 00:35:00.305 align:middle line:84%
where we are, and
what options we have.

00:35:00.305 --> 00:35:02.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I remember some
of those clips, Ben.

00:35:02.180 --> 00:35:05.070 align:middle line:84%
I remember those days,
in the news business,

00:35:05.070 --> 00:35:08.450 align:middle line:84%
or as a younger person,
seeing Mao Tse-tung and Lyndon

00:35:08.450 --> 00:35:09.440 align:middle line:90%
Johnson.

00:35:09.440 --> 00:35:12.335 align:middle line:84%
Those were difficult
times for a lot of people.

00:35:12.335 --> 00:35:13.460 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Yeah, they were.

00:35:13.460 --> 00:35:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And, honestly, those
difficult times

00:35:16.790 --> 00:35:18.770 align:middle line:90%
lead us to where we are today.

00:35:18.770 --> 00:35:20.810 align:middle line:84%
But it also-- this
is where we draw

00:35:20.810 --> 00:35:24.320 align:middle line:90%
on a lot of our inspiration.

00:35:24.320 --> 00:35:27.050 align:middle line:84%
You know, if we
could survive times

00:35:27.050 --> 00:35:29.450 align:middle line:84%
like that, through the Great
Depression and through war,

00:35:29.450 --> 00:35:31.580 align:middle line:84%
we can survive what
we're dealing with today.

00:35:31.580 --> 00:35:33.800 align:middle line:84%
But, like I said in
that clip, we really

00:35:33.800 --> 00:35:36.830 align:middle line:84%
need to have the desire to
overcome these obstacles.

00:35:36.830 --> 00:35:38.550 align:middle line:84%
And I believe the
biggest obstacle

00:35:38.550 --> 00:35:41.040 align:middle line:84%
is, we don't see the
obstacle in front of us.

00:35:41.040 --> 00:35:43.296 align:middle line:84%
We just call it modern
society and living.

00:35:43.296 --> 00:35:45.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: With your little
girl, what will you

00:35:45.170 --> 00:35:50.225 align:middle line:84%
do to her to train her so she's
ready when she's an adult?

00:35:50.225 --> 00:35:52.890 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Really, exactly
what I said before.

00:35:52.890 --> 00:35:54.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to step
out of the way

00:35:54.380 --> 00:35:57.350 align:middle line:84%
and see where her intelligence
naturally takes her.

00:35:57.350 --> 00:36:00.970 align:middle line:84%
But in her path I'm going to
start putting instruments.

00:36:00.970 --> 00:36:02.600 align:middle line:90%
I want her to learn music.

00:36:02.600 --> 00:36:05.870 align:middle line:84%
I want her to use her
voice and sing a lot more.

00:36:05.870 --> 00:36:07.526 align:middle line:84%
Any type of movement
she wants to do.

00:36:07.526 --> 00:36:08.900 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to get
her swimming out

00:36:08.900 --> 00:36:10.940 align:middle line:84%
in nature and in
colder bodies of water,

00:36:10.940 --> 00:36:12.350 align:middle line:90%
climbing through trees.

00:36:12.350 --> 00:36:14.210 align:middle line:84%
And I will be there
to protect her,

00:36:14.210 --> 00:36:16.280 align:middle line:84%
but I will not be
there to limit any

00:36:16.280 --> 00:36:17.930 align:middle line:84%
of where her natural
intelligence is

00:36:17.930 --> 00:36:18.763 align:middle line:90%
trying to bring her.

00:36:18.763 --> 00:36:20.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And when
she's 18 and wants

00:36:20.600 --> 00:36:25.580 align:middle line:84%
to be a teacher or
a rock star, are you

00:36:25.580 --> 00:36:27.260 align:middle line:90%
going to get in the way of that?

00:36:27.260 --> 00:36:29.630 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Absolutely not,
because it doesn't matter

00:36:29.630 --> 00:36:32.150 align:middle line:84%
what profession
you're in or what

00:36:32.150 --> 00:36:33.950 align:middle line:90%
you want to do with your life.

00:36:33.950 --> 00:36:36.180 align:middle line:84%
As long as she's
coming from the heart,

00:36:36.180 --> 00:36:38.780 align:middle line:84%
and as long as she wants to
help the people around her,

00:36:38.780 --> 00:36:40.737 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to be behind her 100%.

00:36:40.737 --> 00:36:42.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What motivates
you here, Ben?

00:36:42.320 --> 00:36:43.624 align:middle line:90%
What pushes you?

00:36:43.624 --> 00:36:45.290 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Knowing
that the world is not

00:36:45.290 --> 00:36:49.280 align:middle line:84%
going to get any better by 7
billion people just sitting

00:36:49.280 --> 00:36:51.890 align:middle line:84%
around waiting for somebody
else to be the super here.

00:36:51.890 --> 00:36:54.050 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not saying
I'm super-human,

00:36:54.050 --> 00:36:55.550 align:middle line:90%
but I'm definitely on that path.

00:36:55.550 --> 00:36:58.880 align:middle line:84%
And I'm also here to show
other people the way.

00:36:58.880 --> 00:37:01.940 align:middle line:84%
You know, I can only say
as much as I've learned.

00:37:01.940 --> 00:37:04.070 align:middle line:84%
But as much as I've
learned I'm going to say.

00:37:04.070 --> 00:37:06.200 align:middle line:90%
And I want to set up a school.

00:37:06.200 --> 00:37:08.690 align:middle line:84%
I want to educate
people with the two best

00:37:08.690 --> 00:37:12.050 align:middle line:84%
forms of nourishment we could be
giving the planet and people--

00:37:12.050 --> 00:37:14.030 align:middle line:90%
and that's love and truth.

00:37:14.030 --> 00:37:16.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We've seen a lot of
the physical that you've done.

00:37:16.820 --> 00:37:19.460 align:middle line:84%
But, as you well know,
and as you've practiced,

00:37:19.460 --> 00:37:22.790 align:middle line:90%
the mind is just as important.

00:37:22.790 --> 00:37:24.590 align:middle line:90%
How do you segue-way the two?

00:37:24.590 --> 00:37:26.480 align:middle line:90%
How does that transition occur--

00:37:26.480 --> 00:37:28.880 align:middle line:84%
the consciousness of the
mind, and the physical,

00:37:28.880 --> 00:37:32.240 align:middle line:90%
built of training and exercise?

00:37:32.240 --> 00:37:34.940 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Again, it's
perspective and belief

00:37:34.940 --> 00:37:36.860 align:middle line:84%
that these two
things are separated.

00:37:36.860 --> 00:37:38.660 align:middle line:84%
It's the way that
we decode reality,

00:37:38.660 --> 00:37:40.820 align:middle line:84%
that we believe our
mind and our bodies

00:37:40.820 --> 00:37:42.690 align:middle line:90%
are in two different categories.

00:37:42.690 --> 00:37:45.950 align:middle line:84%
So, to me, it's really
about not over-thinking

00:37:45.950 --> 00:37:49.220 align:middle line:84%
it-- definitely studying,
but using the body more.

00:37:49.220 --> 00:37:52.720 align:middle line:84%
Because that allows the mind
to calm down a little bit.

00:37:52.720 --> 00:37:55.040 align:middle line:84%
And we don't have to hold
on to every passing thought

00:37:55.040 --> 00:37:55.840 align:middle line:90%
that we have.

00:37:55.840 --> 00:37:57.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's a part of
meditation as well.

00:37:57.720 --> 00:38:00.110 align:middle line:84%
So I say meditation and
movement of the body

00:38:00.110 --> 00:38:03.140 align:middle line:84%
are two great ways to harmonize
the body and the mind.

00:38:03.140 --> 00:38:06.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can this affect
emotion one way or another,

00:38:06.290 --> 00:38:09.890 align:middle line:84%
that if you do this, you're
generally a happier person,

00:38:09.890 --> 00:38:12.590 align:middle line:84%
and that means you'll
reflect that in your living

00:38:12.590 --> 00:38:13.624 align:middle line:90%
with other people?

00:38:13.624 --> 00:38:14.540 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Absolutely.

00:38:14.540 --> 00:38:17.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for one,
exercise in and of itself

00:38:17.330 --> 00:38:20.480 align:middle line:84%
creates a better
hormonal balance.

00:38:20.480 --> 00:38:22.800 align:middle line:84%
And so that's the
hormonal side of it.

00:38:22.800 --> 00:38:26.180 align:middle line:84%
But the deep inner
fulfillment that, I believe,

00:38:26.180 --> 00:38:29.810 align:middle line:90%
happiness really, really needs--

00:38:29.810 --> 00:38:31.460 align:middle line:84%
that deep, inner
fulfillment comes

00:38:31.460 --> 00:38:34.520 align:middle line:84%
from knowing that we're not just
doing something good for us,

00:38:34.520 --> 00:38:36.530 align:middle line:84%
but we're doing something
good for the planet.

00:38:36.530 --> 00:38:38.030 align:middle line:84%
And we're also
looking down the line

00:38:38.030 --> 00:38:40.340 align:middle line:84%
at the next few generations
that are coming.

00:38:40.340 --> 00:38:42.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now everybody
is an individual

00:38:42.440 --> 00:38:45.120 align:middle line:84%
and they have their own
particular likes and dislikes.

00:38:45.120 --> 00:38:47.990 align:middle line:84%
But, in your particular
case, when you meditate,

00:38:47.990 --> 00:38:49.520 align:middle line:90%
what do you do?

00:38:49.520 --> 00:38:53.600 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Only recently have I
done it in the seated position.

00:38:53.600 --> 00:38:56.720 align:middle line:84%
And, really, what I do the
most is I focus on posture.

00:38:56.720 --> 00:38:58.205 align:middle line:84%
And I focus on
everything that's--

00:38:58.205 --> 00:38:59.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Are you comfortable--

00:38:59.150 --> 00:38:59.650 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: --preparatory.

00:38:59.650 --> 00:39:00.765 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --when you do it?

00:39:00.765 --> 00:39:01.640 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Sometimes.

00:39:01.640 --> 00:39:03.999 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes my
body will tell me

00:39:03.999 --> 00:39:05.540 align:middle line:84%
something different
from day to day--

00:39:05.540 --> 00:39:07.790 align:middle line:84%
like there'll be a
twinge in my back.

00:39:07.790 --> 00:39:10.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I'm meditating
on for the next 20 minutes,

00:39:10.400 --> 00:39:12.560 align:middle line:84%
is the fact that my
back isn't comfortable.

00:39:12.560 --> 00:39:15.590 align:middle line:84%
But if I allow myself to
relax, and if I understand

00:39:15.590 --> 00:39:19.700 align:middle line:84%
that correct posture is what
I'm aiming at, then, eventually,

00:39:19.700 --> 00:39:22.610 align:middle line:84%
when I arrive at correct
posture and then that's easy,

00:39:22.610 --> 00:39:23.810 align:middle line:90%
the mind will settle down.

00:39:23.810 --> 00:39:25.910 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of the times,
our mind is so chaotic

00:39:25.910 --> 00:39:28.522 align:middle line:84%
because our body is
receiving so much stimulus

00:39:28.522 --> 00:39:29.480 align:middle line:90%
and we can't sit still.

00:39:29.480 --> 00:39:30.620 align:middle line:90%
We're always fidgeting.

00:39:30.620 --> 00:39:32.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're
still doing music

00:39:32.030 --> 00:39:33.530 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Yes, very much so.

00:39:33.530 --> 00:39:36.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you have been
doing these programs for Gaia

00:39:36.710 --> 00:39:41.330 align:middle line:84%
now for several years,
have you seen, personally,

00:39:41.330 --> 00:39:44.540 align:middle line:84%
an evolution with yourself
in terms of things

00:39:44.540 --> 00:39:47.154 align:middle line:90%
you're learning and changing?

00:39:47.154 --> 00:39:48.070 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Absolutely.

00:39:48.070 --> 00:39:50.970 align:middle line:84%
And Gaia has actually been
a great wealth of knowledge

00:39:50.970 --> 00:39:51.770 align:middle line:90%
for me.

00:39:51.770 --> 00:39:54.217 align:middle line:84%
I go through, and every
free moment I have I

00:39:54.217 --> 00:39:55.550 align:middle line:90%
look through that whole catalog.

00:39:55.550 --> 00:39:57.830 align:middle line:84%
But, yes, through
the past decade

00:39:57.830 --> 00:39:59.450 align:middle line:84%
that I've been
making these films

00:39:59.450 --> 00:40:01.280 align:middle line:84%
and really getting
the word out, I

00:40:01.280 --> 00:40:04.160 align:middle line:84%
would say the best
improvements that I've

00:40:04.160 --> 00:40:06.050 align:middle line:84%
noticed have come
from people who

00:40:06.050 --> 00:40:09.050 align:middle line:84%
send me emails, either
challenging things that I say

00:40:09.050 --> 00:40:11.240 align:middle line:84%
or bringing up just
different ideas.

00:40:11.240 --> 00:40:13.790 align:middle line:84%
So, really, I put
myself out there.

00:40:13.790 --> 00:40:16.640 align:middle line:84%
And people may look at me
as a teacher or a leader.

00:40:16.640 --> 00:40:20.060 align:middle line:84%
But, really, I find myself to
be the student of all the people

00:40:20.060 --> 00:40:22.550 align:middle line:84%
that are sending me
emails, telling me how

00:40:22.550 --> 00:40:23.870 align:middle line:90%
my work has changed their life.

00:40:23.870 --> 00:40:26.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And how do people
e-mail you, by the way?

00:40:26.390 --> 00:40:28.580 align:middle line:10%
>>STEWART:
Talismanicidols@gmail.com.

00:40:28.580 --> 00:40:30.990 align:middle line:10%
And the web site is
talismanicidols.net.

00:40:30.990 --> 00:40:33.650 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And "Kymatica" you
can watch on gaia.com, right?

00:40:33.650 --> 00:40:35.233 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: You can
watch that on Gaia.

00:40:35.233 --> 00:40:38.180 align:middle line:84%
You can watch everything
that I've done on Gaia now.

00:40:38.180 --> 00:40:39.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If there
was one message--

00:40:39.920 --> 00:40:41.690 align:middle line:84%
one message-- that
you would like

00:40:41.690 --> 00:40:44.750 align:middle line:84%
to impart to everybody
watching you today on "Beyond

00:40:44.750 --> 00:40:46.550 align:middle line:90%
Belief," what would that be?

00:40:46.550 --> 00:40:47.840 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Authenticity.

00:40:47.840 --> 00:40:51.350 align:middle line:84%
The more you step and stand
in your own authenticity,

00:40:51.350 --> 00:40:53.450 align:middle line:84%
and be you, no matter
what other people say,

00:40:53.450 --> 00:40:57.170 align:middle line:84%
no matter what kind of box other
people try and fit you into;

00:40:57.170 --> 00:41:01.400 align:middle line:84%
if you carry on in your path
as authentically as possible,

00:41:01.400 --> 00:41:03.710 align:middle line:90%
you are a super-human.

00:41:03.710 --> 00:41:09.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can we survive, as
a species, by doing this,

00:41:09.980 --> 00:41:13.490 align:middle line:84%
in spite of what's
happening on this planet?

00:41:13.490 --> 00:41:16.310 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: Everything that
I've said about the toxins

00:41:16.310 --> 00:41:19.730 align:middle line:84%
in our diets, the problems
of the way we move,

00:41:19.730 --> 00:41:21.530 align:middle line:90%
and the scattered mind--

00:41:21.530 --> 00:41:25.010 align:middle line:84%
if we're not flat out on
the floor because of that,

00:41:25.010 --> 00:41:26.450 align:middle line:84%
we're still up
and moving around,

00:41:26.450 --> 00:41:28.610 align:middle line:84%
building our society
at an astonishing rate.

00:41:28.610 --> 00:41:29.850 align:middle line:90%
So we have a lot of energy.

00:41:29.850 --> 00:41:33.290 align:middle line:84%
What we really need is
just the proper education,

00:41:33.290 --> 00:41:35.120 align:middle line:84%
to focus it on a
better path that's

00:41:35.120 --> 00:41:38.160 align:middle line:84%
actually beneficial for the
planet, not just an elite few

00:41:38.160 --> 00:41:38.960 align:middle line:90%
at the top.

00:41:38.960 --> 00:41:42.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you saw
someone who was unhealthy,

00:41:42.100 --> 00:41:45.140 align:middle line:90%
emotionally and physically--

00:41:45.140 --> 00:41:48.230 align:middle line:84%
probably caused by
their own actions--

00:41:48.230 --> 00:41:50.459 align:middle line:90%
how would you turn them around?

00:41:50.459 --> 00:41:53.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: First, I would start
with just a bunch of questions.

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:54.980 align:middle line:84%
I would see where
their values are-- what

00:41:54.980 --> 00:41:56.810 align:middle line:90%
it is that they actually value.

00:41:56.810 --> 00:42:00.080 align:middle line:84%
And then I would show them
that the answer is just

00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:00.920 align:middle line:90%
the riddle of life.

00:42:00.920 --> 00:42:04.250 align:middle line:84%
Our confusion and when
we're downtrodden--

00:42:04.250 --> 00:42:05.360 align:middle line:90%
that's a riddle.

00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:08.000 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is
inherent within it.

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:10.580 align:middle line:84%
So asking them questions
and getting them

00:42:10.580 --> 00:42:12.950 align:middle line:84%
in their own intelligence
to figure out

00:42:12.950 --> 00:42:14.450 align:middle line:84%
the solution to
their own problem,

00:42:14.450 --> 00:42:15.650 align:middle line:90%
because I don't have it.

00:42:15.650 --> 00:42:16.880 align:middle line:90%
You know, I'm no guru.

00:42:16.880 --> 00:42:19.980 align:middle line:10%
I'm not here to give my message
that other people should

00:42:19.980 --> 00:42:20.780 align:middle line:10%
follow.

00:42:20.780 --> 00:42:24.170 align:middle line:10%
I'm here giving methods to
unleash our own intelligence.

00:42:24.170 --> 00:42:26.557 align:middle line:10%
And that's the way to get out
of any rut that you're in.

00:42:26.557 --> 00:42:28.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Ben, thanks for
being on "Beyond Belief."

00:42:28.640 --> 00:42:29.570 align:middle line:84%
>>STEWART: It's
an honor, George.

00:42:29.570 --> 00:42:32.240 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I look forward
to your shows on Gaia.com.

00:42:32.240 --> 00:42:32.660 align:middle line:90%
>>STEWART: Thank you.

00:42:32.660 --> 00:42:33.320 align:middle line:90%
Me too.

00:42:33.320 --> 00:42:35.690 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: So take the techniques
that Ben has taught us.

00:42:35.690 --> 00:42:38.720 align:middle line:10%
Because we are subject to
the frailties of life-- ups

00:42:38.720 --> 00:42:39.990 align:middle line:10%
and downs.

00:42:39.990 --> 00:42:42.110 align:middle line:84%
But if you learn some
of these techniques,

00:42:42.110 --> 00:42:46.880 align:middle line:84%
physically and emotionally--
what you eat, how you exercise,

00:42:46.880 --> 00:42:49.160 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be
better prepared to combat

00:42:49.160 --> 00:42:50.800 align:middle line:90%
these problems of life.

00:42:50.800 --> 00:42:53.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm George Noory, and thanks
for watching "Beyond Belief."

00:42:53.660 --> 00:42:55.810 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:42:55.810 --> 00:43:00.288 align:middle line:90%